---
description: Payload CMS modeling rules for reusable sites
alwaysApply: true
---

- Prefer block-based page composition through a `layout` field on Pages.
- Use globals for site-wide settings: navigation, theme, SEO defaults, site settings.
- Avoid page-specific hardcoded fields when a reusable block can solve the need.
- Collections should be reusable for future studio sites.
- Use clear slugs and stable field names.
- Keep admin labels editor-friendly.
- Enable preview/live preview where practical.
